accession.name: Accession
accession.desc: Also called an acquisition. A consignment of specimens acquired either by field collecting of staff members, gifts, purchases, or exchange with another institution.

accessionagent.name: Accession Agent
accessionagent.desc: The person(s) requesting the Accession. This references an Agent.

accessionattachment.name: Accession Attachment
accessionattachment.desc: An attachment for the Accession. This may be one or more PDF files of paperwork or a photo of the Accession.

accessionauthorization.name: Accession Authorization
accessionauthorization.desc: This represents the person authorizing the Accession. It references an existing Agent.

address.name: Address
address.desc: The address of an Agent. This also captures a start and end date for the address and the position held while at the address.

addressofrecord.name: Address Of Record
addressofrecord.desc: This is the address when the legal action took place.

agent.name: Agent
agent.desc: Contains information about people, groups, and organizations. Some roles for an agent include collector, determiner, preparer, cataloger, donor, issuer of permits, and so forth.

agentattachment.name: Agent Attachment
agentattachment.desc: This table can be used for a picture of the agent or anything else used to further describe the agent.

agentgeography.name: Agent Geography
agentgeography.desc: The geographical region that a particular collector was known for collecting in.

agentspecialty.name: Agent Specialty
agentspecialty.desc: The Taxonomic specialty that a particular agent was known for.

agentvariant.name: Agent Variant
agentvariant.desc: This is primarily used by Botanists for capturing Variant and Vernacular names. This table is searchable but does not have any specific business rules associated with it.

appraisal.name: Appraisal
appraisal.desc: The monetary appraisal of an Acession or Collection Object

attachment.name: Attachment
attachment.desc: The information in this record identifies everything the application will need to load and display the attachment. The attachment location is an absolute path to the file. The file itself is not stored in the database.

attachmentmetadata.name: Attachment MetadataMetadados
attachmentmetadata.desc: This holds metadata about the attachment. It is a set of named value pairs.

attachmenttag.name: Attachment Tag
attachmenttag.desc: An attribute tag of an attachment. This consists of a single text field for storing a tag. In later versions, users will be allowed to search attachments by their tag.

author.name: Author
author.desc: An Author is a reference to an Agent and provides the order for a list of authors of a Reference Work.

autonumberingscheme.name: Auto Numbering Scheme
autonumberingscheme.desc: This is an internal table used to group parts of a collection with the same numbering scheme.

borrow.name: Borrow
borrow.desc: Contains information about loans from another institution. When one institution borrows a group of objects from another institution, all objects in the borrowed group share a common set of attributes that are defined for the loan.

borrowagent.name: Borrow Agent
borrowagent.desc: Refers to an Agent and describes their role in the borrowing process.

borrowreturnmaterial.name: Borrow Return Material
borrowreturnmaterial.desc: Describes the material that was returned.

collectingevent.name: Collecting Event
collectingevent.desc: A collecting event is a place and time that a collection is made. In some disciplines, a field number is used as the primary designation for place and time information, while in others, locality name and date are used to link specimens.

collectingeventattachment.name: Collecting Event Attachment
collectingeventattachment.desc: Refers to an attachment and provides an order.

collectingeventattribute.name: Collecting Event Attribute
collectingeventattribute.desc: Collecting Event Attributes that were also available in Specify 5.

collectingtrip.name: Collecting Trip
collectingtrip.desc: Used to group Collecting Events together.

collection.name: Collection
collection.desc: A collection holds Collection Objects that are of the same discipline type.

collectionobject.name: Collection Object
collectionobject.desc: A general term for anything that can be a part of your collection: a specimen, a specimen lot, a sound recording, a slide, a tissue, an extract, or a spectrogram.

collectionobjectattachment.name: Collection Object Attachment
collectionobjectattachment.desc: An attachment for a collection object and provides order.

collectionobjectattribute.name: Collection Object Attribute
collectionobjectattribute.desc: Collection Object attributes that were also available in Specify 5.

collectionobjectcitation.name: Collection Object Citation
collectionobjectcitation.desc: Refers to a citation for a Collection Object.

collectionrelationship.name: Collection Relationship
collectionrelationship.desc: Enables two collection objects to refer to each other, for example, voucher and tissue.

collectionreltype.name: Collection Relationship Type
collectionreltype.desc: Describes the type of relationship between two collection objects.

collector.name: Collector
collector.desc: In Specify, the person or persons who collected a specimen. Collector records are stored in the Agent table.

commonnametx.name: Common Name
commonnametx.desc: Describes a common name and the localization of the name. This table is used to describe additional Common Names in other languages.

conservdescription.name: Conservator Description
conservdescription.desc: Describes an object that has participated in a Conservator action. There is only one of these for each Collection Object.

conservdescriptionattachment.name: Conservator Description Attachment
conservdescriptionattachment.desc: Refers to an attachment and provides order.

conservevent.name: Conservator Event
conservevent.desc: An action that takes place as part of a Conservation Description. Over a period of time there may be multiple incidents that require a Conservator to take action.

conserveventattachment.name: Conservator Event Attachment
conserveventattachment.desc: Refers to an attachment and provides order.

container.name: Container
container.desc: A container can optionally be cataloged as a collection object and it contains other collection objects. Describes a logical or physical container.

datatype.name: Data Type
datatype.desc: A data type represents a core type of collection data.

deaccessionnumber.name: Deacc #
deaccessionnumber.desc: Name institution assigns to the deaccession

timestampcreated.name: Timestamp Created
timestampcreated.desc: The timestamp the record was created.

timestampmodified.name: Date Modified
timestampmodified.desc: The timestamp the record was last modified.

type.name: Type
type.desc: Description of the Type of deaccession; i.e. Gift, disposal, lost

deaccession.name: Deaccession
deaccession.desc: Removal of a biological object (specimen, observation, or preparation type) from the collection. Deaccessions may include loans to other collections that are subsequently given to the borrower, lost specimens, and specimens that are destroyed.

timestampcreated.name: Timestamp Created
timestampcreated.desc: The timestamp the record was created.

timestampmodified.name: Timestamp Modified
timestampmodified.desc: The timestamp the record was last modified.

deaccessionagent.name: Deaccession Agent
deaccessionagent.desc: Refers to an agent and contains their role in the deaccession.

determination.name: Determination
determination.desc: The determination of the collection object.

determinationcitation.name: Determination Citation
determinationcitation.desc: Refers to a citation for the determination.

discipline.name: Discipline
discipline.desc: May include one or more collections that share the Taxon, Geography, LithoStratigraphy, and Chronostratigraphy Trees, Localities, Agents and Determination Status.

dnasequence.name: DNA Sequence
dnasequence.desc: Tracks DNA Sequencing information for a Collection Object.

dnasequenceattachment.name: DNA Sequence Attachment
dnasequenceattachment.desc: Refers to an attachment and provides order.

exchangein.name: Exchange In
exchangein.desc: Describes an incoming Exchanged Specimen from a different institution.

exchangeout.name: Exchange Out
exchangeout.desc: Describes an outgoing Exchanged Specimen to a different institution.

fieldnotebookattachment.name: Field Notebook Attachment
fieldnotebookattachment.desc: Refers to an attachment and provides order.

fieldnotebookpage.name: Field Notebook Page
fieldnotebookpage.desc: Describes a page from a Field Note Book.

fieldnotebookpageattachment.name: Field Notebook Page Attachment
fieldnotebookpageattachment.desc: Refers to an attachment and provides order.

fieldnotebookpageset.name: Field Notebook Page Set
fieldnotebookpageset.desc: Describes a set of Field Note Book pages. This can be used to group pages together that were scanned in together.

fieldnotebookpagesetattachment.name: Field Notebook Page Set Attachment
fieldnotebookpagesetattachment.desc: Refers to an attachment and provides order.

geocoorddetail.name: Geo Coord Detail
geocoorddetail.desc: Describes extra detail for a Locality for Manis data.

geography.name: Geography
geography.desc: Represents politcal boundary (Country, State, County, Township, etc.).

geographytreedef.name: Geography Tree Definition
geographytreedef.desc: Defines the levels of the Geography tree.

geographytreedefitem.name: Geography Tree Definition Item
geographytreedefitem.desc: Describes a level in the definition of the tree.

geologictimeperiodtreedef.name: Geological Time Period Tree Definition
geologictimeperiodtreedef.desc: Defines the levels of the GTP tree.

geologictimeperiodtreedefitem.name: Geological Time Period Tree Definition Item
geologictimeperiodtreedefitem.desc: Describes a level in the definition of the tree.

giftagent.name: Gift Agent
giftagent.desc: Describes the role the Agent played in the giving of a Gift.

giftpreparation.name: Gift Preparation
giftpreparation.desc: Points a gift to a preparation.

groupperson.name: Group Person
groupperson.desc: This is a join table for Agents that are Institutions and Organizations that contain other Agents. It also provides order.

inforequest.name: Information Request
inforequest.desc: Describes a request for information on a collection and refers to a Bundle of Collection Objects.

institution.name: Institution
institution.desc: The parent institution. An institution is made up of one or more divisions.

lithostrattreedef.name: Lithostratigraphy Tree Definition
lithostrattreedef.desc: Defines the levels of the tree.

lithostrattreedefitem.name: Lithostratigraphy Tree Definition Item
lithostrattreedefitem.desc: Describes a level in the definition of the tree.

loan.name: Loan
loan.desc: A group of specimens that another institution borrows from your collection. Specify lets you manage all aspects of loans electronically so that you always have an up-to-date record of which specimen have been loaned and which have been returned.

loanagent.name: Loan Agent
loanagent.desc: An agent associated with a loan. Each agent includes the role played in the loan process.

loanattachment.name: Loan Attachment
loanattachment.desc: Refers to an attachment and provides order.

loanpreparation.name: Loan Preparation
loanpreparation.desc: A join table between the Loan and the Preparation. It contains comments and quantity fields.

loanreturnpreparation.name: Loan Return Preparation
loanreturnpreparation.desc: This is used for tracking a returned Preparation for a loan.

locality.name: Locality
locality.desc: The name of the location where a specimen was collected or observed. Some taxonomic disciplines or collectors may use a locality name instead of a field number to associate a collecting event with a specimen.

localityattachment.name: Locality Attachment
localityattachment.desc: Refers to an attachment and provides order.

localitycitation.name: Locality Citation
localitycitation.desc: A join table to link a Locality to a Citation.

localitydetail.name: Locality Detail
localitydetail.desc: Describes additional Locality detail. For example, water body and island information. Includes UTM fields.

localitynamealias.name: Locality Name Alias
localitynamealias.desc: Describes additional names for a given Locality.

otheridentifier.name: Other Identifier
otheridentifier.desc: Describes an identifier (Catalog Number) of a Collection Object from a different Institution.

paleocontext.name: Paleo Context
paleocontext.desc: Describes the paleontologic information for a Collection Object. This also references Chronostratigraphy and Bio Stratigray.

permit.name: Permit
permit.desc: The permit transaction window is designed to hold information linked to legal paperwork for permission from a government agency to collect a specimen or specimens. Preparation: A subdivision of a collection object that refers to the preparation method.

permitattachment.name: Permit Attachment
permitattachment.desc: Refers to an attachment and provides order.

picklist.name: Pick List
picklist.desc: System Table: A list of items that can be choosen to produce a controlled vocabulary.

preparation.name: Preparation
preparation.desc: Preparation information describes the physical status of a specimen and its storage media. Specify provides an extensive array of utilities for curatorial management of specimen preparations.

preparationattachment.name: Preparation Attachment
preparationattachment.desc: Refers to an attachment and provides order.

preparationattribute.name: Preparation Attribute
preparationattribute.desc: Preparation attributes that were also available in Specify 5.

preptype.name: Preparation Type
preptype.desc: Describe a Preparation Type. For example, Cleared and Stained, Mounted, etc.

project.name: Project
project.desc: Describes a grouping of Collection Objects.

recordset.name: Record Set
recordset.desc: Describes a set of records of any type that can be acted upon within the applicatiton.

repositoryagreement.name: Repository Agreement
repositoryagreement.desc: An agreement for allowing an Accession to occur, but does not include ownership.

repositoryagreementattachment.name: Repository Agreement Attachment
repositoryagreementattachment.desc: Refers to an attachment and provides order.

shipment.name: Shipment
shipment.desc: Describes the shipment of a Loan or Exchange.

spappresource.name: App Resource
spappresource.desc: System Table: This represents a resource, typically XML, that the application uses during run time.

spappresourcedata.name: App Resource Data
spappresourcedata.desc: System Table: The data associated with an application resource.

spappresourcedir.name: App Resource Default
spappresourcedir.desc: System Table: the default for application resources.

specifyuser.name: Specify User
specifyuser.desc: System Table: This represents Specify User within the application.

spfieldvaluedefault.name: Sp Field Value Default
spfieldvaluedefault.desc: System Table: This represents a default field value for a form.

splocalecontainer.name: Locale Container
splocalecontainer.desc: System Table: This is used for localizing the database schema it has a localized name and description but can also contain localizable items.

splocalecontaineritem.name: Locale Container Item
splocalecontaineritem.desc: System Table: This is used for localizing the database schema it has a localized name and description.

splocaleitemstr.name: Locale Item String
splocaleitemstr.desc: System Table: This is used for localizing the database schema it represents a string and also a Language, Country and Variant for that string.

spquery.name: Sp Query
spquery.desc: System Table: This represents a saved Query.

spqueryfield.name: Sp Query Field
spqueryfield.desc: System Table: This represents a single field in a saved Query.

spreport.name: Sp Report
spreport.desc: System Table: This represents a saved Report.

spviewsetobj.name: View Set Object
spviewsetobj.desc: System Table: This represents a View Set used in the form system.

storage.name: Storage
storage.desc: A tree data structure for describing where Collection Objects are physically stored.

storagetreedef.name: Storage Tree Definition
storagetreedef.desc: Defines the levels of the tree.

storagetreedefitem.name: Storage Tree Definition Item
storagetreedefitem.desc: Describes a level in the definition of the tree.

taxon.name: Taxon
taxon.desc: Describes the taxonomy of a Determination.

taxonattachment.name: Taxon Attachment
taxonattachment.desc: This refers to an attachment and provides order.

taxoncitation.name: Taxon Citation
taxoncitation.desc: Linkage from the Taxonomic record to a published document.

taxontreedef.name: Taxon Tree Definition
taxontreedef.desc: Defines the levels of the tree.

taxontreedefitem.name: Taxon Tree Definition Item
taxontreedefitem.desc: Describes a level in the definition of the tree.

treatmentevent.name: Treatment Event
treatmentevent.desc: An action that occurs to a Conservation Description.

workbenchrowimage.name: Workbench Row Image
workbenchrowimage.desc: An image associated with a row.

workbenchtemplate.name: WorkBench Template
workbenchtemplate.desc: The mapping description of the WorkBench.

workbenchtemplatemappingitem.name: WorkBench Template Mapping Item
workbenchtemplatemappingitem.desc: One column of the mapped description.
